"Functional Unit
To obtain 1kg of canned vegetable or fruit. 
An input of 0,626kg of food is required. Added packaging should account for the 1% loss.

From peeled fruit or vegetable to canned product: food slicing, can filling (38% water) and sterilization. 1% loss rate is applied at the end. we considered 50% of canned vegetables (with a blanching step) and 50% of canned fruits (without any blanching) to model the canning process."

About 56 percent of the work on the farm is done by family members.
